net.sourceforge.waters.model.marshaller

Class StandardExtensionFileFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • javax.swing.filechooser.FileFilter
      • net.sourceforge.waters.model.marshaller.StandardExtensionFileFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    FileFilter

    public class StandardExtensionFileFilter
extends FileFilter
implements FileFilter
    A simple file filter for use with Swing's file chooser, to match file names with a single extension.
    See Also:
    JFileChooser

      • StandardExtensionFileFilter

        public StandardExtensionFileFilter(String description,
                                   String ext)
        Creates a new file filter that accepts directories in addition to files with the given extension.
        Parameters:
        description - A textual description of the files accepted by this filter, to be displayed in the file chooser's file type selection box.
        ext - The filename extension accepted by the filter, with preceding dot.

      • StandardExtensionFileFilter

        public StandardExtensionFileFilter(String description,
                                   String ext,
                                   boolean dirs)
        Creates a new file filter.
        Parameters:
        description - A textual description of the files accepted by this filter, to be displayed in the file chooser's file type selection box.
        ext - The filename extension accepted by the filter, with preceding dot.
        dirs - A flag, indicating that the filter accepts all directories in addition to files with the given extension.

    • Method Detail

      • getFilter

        public static StandardExtensionFileFilter getFilter(String description,
                                                    String ext)
        Returns a file filter for a given extension. This method tries to ensure that only one file filter object is created for any given type, by creating a lookup table indexed by the extension. If a file filter with a given extension is found, that object is returned, ignoring the description.
        Parameters:
        description - A textual description of the files accepted by this filter, to be displayed in the file chooser's file type selection box.
        ext - The filename extension accepted by the filter, with preceding dot.

        public File ensureDefaultExtension(File file)
        Ensures that the given file name has an extension. If the file name part of the path does not include any dot character, the filter's default extension is appended.
        Parameters:
        file - The file name to be checked.
        Returns:
        A file with extension appended if necessary.
